Given an int and add up the individual digits of the int and return the solution. 

namespace AddingDigits
{
    class Program
    {
        public static int AddingDigits(int input)
        {
            int output = 0;

            while(input != 0)
            {
                output += input % 10;
                input = input / 10;
            }
            return output;
        }
        
        
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(AddingDigits(-154));
        }
    }
}

This solution was found with the help of Tim Weigel. I have trouble wrapping my mind around the modulus operator, Tim tried his best to help me only time will tell.
